The person who has no self-nature, can be regarded as a single one. It is not that it does not exist in any of these three ways: (1) 
the object which exists through another's own mind; (2) the subject whose existence is also known by oneself or otherness; 
(3) the object which exists without this body nor itself ; (4) the object whose essence is seen by others; (5) the object 
which exists through another’s mind; (6) the object having been described by him; (7) the object being 
known by himself; (8) the object possessing an external world; (9) the object with its objects;

