It’s when someone doesn’t know that way. … 
When you don’t understand this, they will be reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm. They are extinguished there, or are not liable to return from it. 
This is called the relation of suffering and happiness. 
And what is the distinction between life and death? 
The practice for which gentlemen rightly go forth from these four grounds: 
the training of those who live with possessions ended; 
and the training of those accomplished ones; 
those who die without wishes ended; iaving with nothing left behind; 
they experience pleasure as loss of body, speech, and mind.
